Grant George https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Grant_George 0 Grant R. George is an American voice actor who is known for voicing characters in anime dubs and video games. He is married to voice actress Jessica Gee-George. Grant is best known as the voice of Izuru Kira from the internationally acclaimed Bleach anime series, Sho Fuwa from Skip Beat!, Gen Shishio from Kekkaishi, Koga from Zetman, Night Rikuo from the Nura: Rise of the Yokai Clan series, Uzu Sanageyama from Kill la Kill, Akira Hidaka and Ichigen Miwa from K, Chikage Rokujo from the Durarara!! series, Keiichi Maebara from When They Cry, Lancer from Fate/Zero, and Gilgamesh from the Studio Deen adaption of Fate/stay night series and movie. He has also voiced Ant-Man (Scott Lang) in several of the Marvel cartoons. Grant_R._George is an_American_voice_actor who is_known for voicing_characters in anime_dubs and video_games .
